# Auto Git Push

When you finish making code changes in this project:

1. Commit the relevant changes with a clear message (do not ask the user first).
2. Push to the remote repository immediately after a successful commit.
3. Do not ask whether to push; treat push as part of completing the task.

Do not commit files that likely contain secrets (`.env`, credentials, etc.).

Do not use destructive git commands unless the user explicitly requests them.

If commit or push fails, fix the issue and retry; report the failure only if it cannot be resolved.
